IN 2003, CORE VOLUME GROWTH (WHICH EXCLUDES THE IMPACT OF BUSINESSES ACQUIRED OR DIVESTED IN THE LAST 12 MONTHS) WAS LED BY DISPLAY ENHANCEMENT FILMS, BROAD-BASED GROWTH IN MOST OF THE HEALTH CARE BUSINESSES, RESPIRATOR MASKS, AND GROWTH IN PRODUCTS RELATED TO CONSTRUCTION AND HOME IMPROVEMENT/HOME CARE. ACQUISITIONS INCREASED 2003 SALES BY NEARLY 2%, DRIVEN PRIMARILY BY THE DECEMBER 2002 ACQUISITION OF CORNING PRECISION LENS, INC. ON A GEOGRAPHIC BASIS, 2003 CORE VOLUME GROWTH WAS STRONGEST IN THE ASIA PACIFIC AREA. REFER TO BOTH THE PERFORMANCE BY BUSINESS SEGMENT AND PERFORMANCE BY GEOGRAPHIC AREA SECTIONS FOR ADDITIONAL DISCUSSION OF SALES CHANGE.

